<br>
Technically, Darkguard still exists.  There are a few alts that still bear the tag.  But for guilds like Imperium &amp; Darkguard to take a raid slot on dragons is ubsurd, and basically abuse.  If every guild that has at least 1 character over 40 signed up for Nagafen &amp; Vox, the lists would be stupidly long. (Think VS)  There's already enough dead weight on the lists.<br>
<br>
If we want to keep rotations working well on Brell, we have to be serious about not abusing the rotations.  Everyone and their dog can't get a raid slot if we want the system to work smoothly.  That means that guilds of fewer than 10 45-52 people really shouldn't be on the dragon lists.  Guilds with fewer than 10 people over 55 shouldn't be on the Trak list.  Indies really shouldn't be on either.  If you're in a guild with fewer than 10, consider grouping together with another similar guild &amp; getting a rotation slot together.<br>
<br>
When a rotation starts to go over 4 months, the system will start to break down.  Do your part be honest with yourself, in order to keep the rotation moving along smoothly. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukallikamerov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kalli Kamerov</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Guardian of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 517<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/16/01 2:33:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://images.honesty.com/imagedata/h/895/90/28959015.jpg width = 135 height = 184></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Indies on more than one list</span><hr size=1> Unless I'm mistaken Borammer is now in Exile....<br>
