 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udaveonsilverstring.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daveon Silverstring</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 60<br> <font color=#CC9900>(5/24/01 1:08:20 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.com/mcheeks/everquest/daveon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Indies on more than one list</span><hr size=1> That's not exactly true.<br>
<br>
People tend to forget that if a guild is only fielding 1/3 of the raid party, the other 2/3 of the raid crew they invite are still rolling on the items.  I've seen dragon raids where no one in the hosting guild won anything.<br>
<br>
So in the situation where 3 guilds each provide 1/3 the raid crew for 1 raid, each guild has a 1/3 chance on items (I'm simplifying it little here to make my point).<br>
<br>
Whereas if those same 3 guilds hold different raids, the guilds STILL only have a 1/3 chance on items, because the other 2/3 of the raiders they invite aren't just going to sit there and not roll on something.<br>
<br>
The exception here is if a guild claims something for itself as loot.  So if each of the 3 guilds claimed something, then yes, they are each guaranteed an item (IF it drops, that is).  Of course, there is nothing stopping them from teaming up with guilds that wish to claim a different item (or not claim any!) and working it out with the other guild(s) beforehand.<br>
<br>
By the same token, a guild that can field 100% of the raid crew gets 100% of the items.<br>
<br>
<br>
I definitely believe that small guilds should work together and team up on the dragon lists.  It would make the lists go faster.  I just think people should do it in the spirit of shortening the lists, rather than a perceived loot issue.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p><b>--Daveon Silverstring<br>
